article.headline: Tennessee Tech 77, Tennessee State 76
article.story: COOKEVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Cameron Crisp scored 29 points to lead Tennessee Tech to a 90-83 double-overtime victory over Samford on Thursday night. Tennessee Tech (11-9, 5-4 Ohio Valley Conference) trailed by five points twice in the first overtime period, but managed to tie the game at 62 on a Willie Jenkins tip-in with two-tenths of a second to play. Samford (10-10, 5-4) pulled ahead 78-73 with 2:56 left in the second overtime on two Eddie Harper free throws. Tennessee Tech responded with a 13-0 run to go up 86-78 with 37 seconds left. Crisp scored five points during the run, including a 3-pointer, and Will Moore shot 4-for-4 from the free-throw line. The Golden Eagles lost a 53-39 lead when Samford went on a 22-5 run with just under nine minutes to play in regulation. The run was sparked by two Tyson Dorsey 3-pointers and capped by a Phillip Ramelli basket with two minutes left to put Samford up 61-58. Jenkins scored 18 points and grabbed 10 rebounds for Tennessee Tech, while Milone Clark scored 15 points and Keyon Boyd added 13. Harper led the Bulldogs with 22 points. Ramelli had 18 and J. Robert Merritt and Dorsey each added 14.
